=== Noun ===
'''road'''
# A [[narrow]] strip of [[land]] made suitable for [[travel]] between [[places]]. Modern roads are usually paved to accommodate wheeled [[vehicle]]s.
# By extension, the [[path]] or [[route]] one takes; an [[effort]]
#:''Learning English is a long '''road''' for newcomers.''

===Prepositions===
The term road is used with the preposition [[on]]. Something is on the road, but [[in]] the [[street]].

